__data__.text:
assistant: 1. Turn on the lights in the kitchen and dining room.
2. Inspect the kitchen countertops and dining tables to identify misplaced items.
3. Identify the carton of milk, bottle of water, mug, glass, wine glass, plate, knife, book, laptop, bowl of lemons, pot, box of crackers, jar, box of rice bubbles, box of Jello, and box of Alpen Salt.
4. Locate the standard storage locations for each type of item in the kitchen.
5. Put the carton of milk in the refrigerator.
6. Put the bottle of water in the refrigerator.
7. Put the mug, glass, wine glass, and plate in the dark grey cabinets above the countertop.
8. Put the knife in the designated knife storage in the dark grey cabinets.
9. Put the book and laptop on a designated shelf or area away from the dining table.
10. Put the bowl of lemons on the countertop near the sink or in the refrigerator.
11. Put the pot on the stove or in the designated pot storage.
12. Put the box of crackers, box of rice bubbles, box of Jello, and box of Alpen Salt in the dark grey cabinets.
13. Put the jar in the dark grey cabinets.
14. Inspect the kitchen and dining room to ensure all misplaced items have been returned to their standard storage locations.
15. Turn off the lights if necessary.
